Citation.sTitle: Excess molar volume along with viscosity, refractive index and relative permittivity for binary mixtures of exo-tetrahydrodicyclopentadiene with four octane isomers
Citation.sAbstract: The fundamental physical properties including density, viscosity, refractive index and relative permittivity, have been measured for binary mixtures of exo-tetrahydrodicyclopentadiene (JP-10) with four octane isomers (n-octane, 3-methylheptane, 2,4-dimethylhexane and 2,2,4-trimethylpentane) over the whole composition range at temperatures T = (293.15 to 313.15) K and pressure p = 0.1 MPa. The values of excess molar volume VE m  , viscosity deviation (Dg), refractive index deviation (DnD) and relative permittivity deviation (Der) are then calculated. All of the values of VE m and Dg are observed to be negative, while those of DnD and Der are close to zero. The effects of temperature and composition on the variation of VE m values are discussed. The negative values of VE m and Dg are conductive to high-density and lowresistance of fuels, which is favorable for the design and preparation of advanced hydrocarbon fuels.
